{
  "texts": [
    "Outliers in time series are data are points that are significantly high or low from the overall range.",
    "They can be identified using statistical measures like Dixon's test [34], Grubb's Test [35] and z-scores [36].",
    "Outliers are values recorded due to measurement errors, data entry mistakes, or changes in underlying processes.",
    "Outliers are significantly low in the datasets and are not points of interest so they can be treated by removal.",
    "On the other hand extreme values though very little are in considerable proportion due to which they can not be removed."
  ]
}